Installation Instructions
*************************

This file is free documentation; the Free Software Foundation gives
unlimited permission to copy, distribute and modify it.

Basic Installation
==================

Briefly, the shell commands `make clean all' should
build both the library and demo application.  The following
more-detailed instructions are generic; see the `README' file for
instructions specific to this package.

The simplest way to compile this package is:

  1. `cd' to the directory containing the package's source code and type
     `make lib' to build the library.

  2. Type `make demo' to build the dema application.

  3. You can remove the program binaries and object files from the
     source code directory by typing `make clean'.

